<subSubSection box="[197,1142,1125,1151]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1338]" box="[197,1142,1125,1151]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1125,1151]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the black median part of the hind femur.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1338]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1162,1188]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Saigusa, 1963" authorityName="Saigusa" authorityYear="1963" box="[756,1148,1162,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Hybos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloripes">
<emphasis box="[756,971,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Hybos bicoloripes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Saigusa" box="[979,1148,1162,1188]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" refString="Saigusa, T. (1963) Systematic studies of the genus Hybos in Japan I. New species with yellowish legs (Diptera, Empididae). Sieboldia, 3 (1), 97 - 104." type="journal article" year="1963">
Saigusa, 
<number box="[1086,1148,1162,1188]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it may be separated from the latter by the coxae and trochanters black, wing dark brown at apex of the basal cells and anal cell, and the left surstylus strongly curved inward. In 
<taxonomicName box="[715,883,1238,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Hybos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloripes">
<emphasis box="[715,883,1238,1263]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">H. bicoloripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the coxae and trochanters are yellow, the wing is not dark brown at apex of the basal cells and anal cell, and the left surstylus is nearly straight (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Yang, C. K. (2004) Diptera, Empididae, Hemerodromiinae Hybotinae. Fauna Sinica Insecta, Vol. 34. Science Press, Beijing, 1 - 329." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Yang &amp; Yang 
<number box="[151,215,1312,1338]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
